The paper deals with image registration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of principal component analysis (PCA) and an integrated model for pathology removal and image reconstruction suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of low-rank/sparse (LRS) decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The mention of blurring and image reconstruction suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient alternative to LRS, which may involve optimization techniques, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
